
>Reload the RVM
rvm reload

>Install Ruby 1.9.3-p125
rvm install ruby-1.9.3-p125

> List rubies to know what all versions of ruby you have
rvm list rubies

> Create a gemset for Rails 3.2
rvm gemset create 'rails32'

> Bind Ruby 1.9.3-p125 with that gemset 
rvm ruby-1.9.3-p125@rails32

> Install Rails
gem install rails -v "=3.2"

> List all rails versions
gem list rails

> Create Our Hr Man Project
rails new hr_man

> Create rvmrc file
echo "rvm ruby-1.9.3-p125@rails32" > .rvmrc

> Look at the Rails version
rails -v

> Look at the Ruby version
ruby -v 

> Do Bundle Install if you have not done that
bundle install

> Install the following if installer specifies you to install
gem install coffee-script-source -v '1.2.0'

> Start the Rails Server in port 4000
rails s -p4000

Now Get Ready for Code!!!!

